1. Tool Authorization

```python
class ToolPolicy:
    def can_execute(self, tool_name: str, context: Context) -> bool:
        # User-level permissions
        if tool_name in self.restricted_tools:
            return context.user.has_permission(tool_name)

        # Rate limiting
        if self.rate_limiter.is_exceeded(context.user.id, tool_name):
            return False

        # Time-based restrictions
        if tool_name == "deploy_production" and not self.is_business_hours():
            return False

        return True
```

3. Output Validation

Run agent outputs through validation layers:

```python
class ValidationPipeline:
    def validate(self, output: AgentOutput) -> ValidationResult:
        # Semantic validation
        if not self.semantic_validator.check(output):
            return ValidationResult.fail("Semantic inconsistency detected")

        # Safety check
        if self.safety_classifier.is_unsafe(output.text):
            return ValidationResult.fail("Safety policy violation")

        # Factual verification (for claims)
        if output.contains_claims:
            verification = self.fact_checker.verify(output.claims)
            if verification.confidence < 0.7:
                return ValidationResult.uncertain("Fact check inconclusive")

        return ValidationResult.pass_()
```

Model Routing

Not every task needs GPT-4. Implement a routing layer:

```python
class ModelRouter:
    def route(self, task: Task) -> ModelConfig:
        if task.complexity_score < 0.3:
            return ModelConfig(model="gpt-3.5-turbo", temp=0.1)  # Fast, cheap
        elif task.requires_reasoning:
            return ModelConfig(model="claude-3-opus", temp=0.2)  # Best reasoning
        elif task.requires_creativity:
            return ModelConfig(model="gpt-4-turbo", temp=0.7)   # Creative
        else:
            return ModelConfig(model="gpt-4", temp=0.2)         # Default
```

This reduces costs by 65% with `<5%` quality degradation.
